Quote:  ACAENA SANGUISORBAE (<i>Vahl</i> .) The Native Burr. ... The `HUTIWAI', or `PIRIPIRI'.- ... an infusion of the leaves is said to afford a substitute for tea, but it is the opinion of the writer that the results are not commensurate with the trouble of brewing.
